---
// Funder's Slate Audit Checklist — grounded in established creative-economy
// inclusion standards: BFI Diversity Standards (used for ~£500M of UK film
// funding), the Annenberg Inclusion Initiative's measurement framework, and
// Eurimages gender-equality criteria. Adapted to surface the gender-norm
// decisions implicit in a slate's evaluation pipeline.
---
<div class="panel p-6 md:p-10 print:bg-white print:text-black">
  <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-gold-400">Funder's Slate Audit Checklist</p>
  <h3 class="mt-1 font-display text-2xl text-white">
    10 questions to ask of a slate before you commit.
  </h3>
  <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-white/60 max-w-2xl">
    Built on three industry-standard frameworks:
    <span class="text-white">BFI Diversity Standards</span> (the four-pillar
    model used to qualify projects for UK public film funding),
    <span class="text-white">the Annenberg Inclusion Initiative</span>
    measurement framework (USC's annual studies on screen and behind-the-camera
    representation), and
    <span class="text-white">Eurimages gender-equality criteria</span> (the
    Council of Europe co-production fund's gender-bonus mechanism). Each
    question below maps to one of those frameworks and translates it into a
    decision a fund officer can put on a slate review agenda.
  </p>

  <ol class="mt-8 grid gap-3 md:grid-cols-2 text-sm leading-relaxed">
    <!-- Pillar A — On-screen representation (BFI Standard A; Annenberg Inclusion Initiative) -->
    <li class="rounded-lg bg-ink-950/40 ring-1 ring-white/5 px-4 py-3">
      <p class="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-gold-400/70 mb-1">A · On-screen representation</p>
      <span class="font-display text-gold-400 text-xs">01.</span>
      <span class="ml-2 text-white/85">Across the slate, how are screen time and speaking time distributed by gender? <span class="text-white/55">(Annenberg's standard cut: % of speaking characters who are female; GD-IQ benchmark.)</span></span>
    </li>
    <li class="rounded-lg bg-ink-950/40 ring-1 ring-white/5 px-4 py-3">
      <p class="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-gold-400/70 mb-1">A · On-screen representation</p>
      <span class="font-display text-gold-400 text-xs">02.</span>
      <span class="ml-2 text-white/85">Which projects clear an inclusion floor — Bechdel–Wallace, GD-IQ female speaking time ≥ 50%, or your fund's named threshold?</span>
    </li>

    <!-- Pillar B — Creative leadership (BFI Standard B; Eurimages gender bonus) -->
    <li class="rounded-lg bg-ink-950/40 ring-1 ring-white/5 px-4 py-3">
      <p class="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-gold-400/70 mb-1">B · Creative leadership</p>
      <span class="font-display text-gold-400 text-xs">03.</span>
      <span class="ml-2 text-white/85">What share of director, writer, and producer credits across the slate are women? <span class="text-white/55">(Eurimages awards a bonus when 5 of 8 key creative roles are filled by women — what's your equivalent?)</span></span>
    </li>
    <li class="rounded-lg bg-ink-950/40 ring-1 ring-white/5 px-4 py-3">
      <p class="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-gold-400/70 mb-1">B · Creative leadership</p>
      <span class="font-display text-gold-400 text-xs">04.</span>
      <span class="ml-2 text-white/85">For projects depicting trauma — harassment, abuse, sexual violence, domestic violence — is a woman in a key creative leadership role (director, writer, or showrunner)?</span>
    </li>

    <!-- Pillar C — Industry opportunity / talent pipeline (BFI Standard C; inclusion riders) -->
    <li class="rounded-lg bg-ink-950/40 ring-1 ring-white/5 px-4 py-3">
      <p class="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-gold-400/70 mb-1">C · Industry opportunity</p>
      <span class="font-display text-gold-400 text-xs">05.</span>
      <span class="ml-2 text-white/85">Does the slate include first-time directors, women DPs and editors, and other under-represented heads of department? <span class="text-white/55">(BFI Standard C; Stacy Smith's inclusion-rider language.)</span></span>
    </li>
    <li class="rounded-lg bg-ink-950/40 ring-1 ring-white/5 px-4 py-3">
      <p class="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-gold-400/70 mb-1">C · Industry opportunity</p>
      <span class="font-display text-gold-400 text-xs">06.</span>
      <span class="ml-2 text-white/85">Are paid training, shadowing, or mentorship roles embedded in the productions you're funding — and tracked as a deliverable, not as a hope?</span>
    </li>

    <!-- Pillar D — Norm shaping & audience (the MAPGEN extension; BFI Standard D + Annenberg ROI work) -->
    <li class="rounded-lg bg-ink-950/40 ring-1 ring-white/5 px-4 py-3">
      <p class="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-gold-400/70 mb-1">D · Norm shaping & audience</p>
      <span class="font-display text-gold-400 text-xs">07.</span>
      <span class="ml-2 text-white/85">Across the slate, who tends to feel <em>shame</em>, and for what? Who tends to feel <em>pride</em>, and for what? Does the aggregate pattern match what your fund publicly says it stands for?</span>
    </li>
    <li class="rounded-lg bg-ink-950/40 ring-1 ring-white/5 px-4 py-3">
      <p class="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-gold-400/70 mb-1">D · Norm shaping & audience</p>
      <span class="font-display text-gold-400 text-xs">08.</span>
      <span class="ml-2 text-white/85">Which projects amplify the dominant norms of their region's cinema, and which complicate them? Is the balance intentional?</span>
    </li>
    <li class="rounded-lg bg-ink-950/40 ring-1 ring-white/5 px-4 py-3">
      <p class="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-gold-400/70 mb-1">D · Norm shaping & audience</p>
      <span class="font-display text-gold-400 text-xs">09.</span>
      <span class="ml-2 text-white/85">For projects with norm-shifting content, is there a distribution and marketing plan that reaches the audience the project was designed for? <span class="text-white/55">(Annenberg's box-office work shows that inclusive films perform — when they're released widely.)</span></span>
    </li>
    <li class="rounded-lg bg-ink-950/40 ring-1 ring-white/5 px-4 py-3">
      <p class="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-gold-400/70 mb-1">D · Norm shaping & audience</p>
      <span class="font-display text-gold-400 text-xs">10.</span>
      <span class="ml-2 text-white/85">A year from release, what would you want to be able to say this slate moved — and how will you measure it (audience surveys, content audit, longitudinal RCT)?</span>
    </li>
  </ol>

  <p class="mt-6 text-xs text-white/45 max-w-3xl leading-relaxed">
    <span class="text-white/60">Sources:</span>
    BFI Diversity Standards
    (<a href="https://www.bfi.org.uk/inclusion-film-industry/bfi-diversity-standards" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-gold-400/80 hover:underline">bfi.org.uk</a>);
    Annenberg Inclusion Initiative annual reports
    (<a href="https://annenberg.usc.edu/research/aii" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-gold-400/80 hover:underline">annenberg.usc.edu</a>);
    Eurimages gender-equality strategy
    (<a href="https://www.coe.int/en/web/eurimages/gender-equality" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-gold-400/80 hover:underline">coe.int</a>);
    Geena Davis Inclusion Quotient (GD-IQ);
    Stacy Smith / Annenberg inclusion-rider template.
  </p>

  <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3 text-xs text-white/40">
    <button onclick="window.print()" class="rounded-full bg-white/5 px-4 py-2 text-white/70 ring-1 ring-white/10 hover:bg-white/10 hover:text-white transition print:hidden">
      Print this checklist
    </button>
    <span>or screenshot — it's CC-BY.</span>
  </div>
</div>
